# Pack authoring rules

Full background is in [`docs/spec.md`](../../docs/spec.md) §5 and §6.3. The legal separation between pack types is in §9.2.

## Two pack types — do not mix

- **`*.tpack.yaml`** — **Template Pack.** Templates, counter definitions, macros, page presets. **Our creative work.** Can be bundled with the app. License: MIT or CC-BY-4.0.
- **`*.dpack.yaml`** — **Data Pack.** Concrete entities (spells, classes, items) with game text. **Third-party content.** Never bundled with the app. License inherited from source.

**A single file is either a template pack or a data pack. Never both.**

## Envelope

Every pack starts with a `pack:` header declaring `type`, `id`, `name`, `version`, `license`, `author`, and (for data packs) `requires:` listing template packs it depends on.

## Rules

- **No executable code in packs.** No formulas, no scripts, no `modifier_expr` fields. User-entered value pairs only (see spec §5.3 and §11).
- **Every data pack declares `license:` and `attribution:`.** Must match the source's licence. `codex-pack validate` will enforce this.
- **Versioning is SemVer:** `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`. Major = breaking template changes.
- **Don't edit bundled template packs casually.** Breaking changes need an ADR and a major version bump.
- **Prefer fine-grained entities.** A class feature is its own entity, referenced by both the class entity and the character — never inlined.

## Required fields on entities

Only `id`, `template_id`, and `name` are required. Everything else is optional; the renderer handles missing fields silently.
